messages.user_message: What is the appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Carbon?
messages.assistant_response: The appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Carbon Fibre (CF) is 205, 215, or 225°C. For PLA mixed with continuous carbon fibre (CCF) or short carbon fibre (SCF), the nozzle temperature is 210 or 250°C. This information is sourced from the "Enhanced Table Data" document.
